Diagnosis.
Funicle relatively compact with antennomeres 2 and 3 subequal (
Fig. 5A
). Sides of the prosternal process converging anteriorly (
Fig. 5B
). Aedeagus in lateral view with apex of phallobase obliquely oriented and penis about as wide as base of posterior quarter (
Fig. 6A–B
).
